        <h2>How Our Technicians Repair a Bosch Wall Oven</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="process-grid">
        <div class="process-step">
          <div class="step-num">1</div>
          <h3>Scope the Job Before Disassembly</h3>
          <p>Most wall oven repairs happen in the cabinet — no extraction
          needed. We scope the failure before pulling anything, so we don't
          drop a 200 lb oven out of custom cabinetry for a $220 thermistor
          swap that's front-accessible.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <div class="step-num">2</div>
          <h3>Test, Don't Guess</h3>
          <p>Before a bake element goes in, we ohm-test the existing one.
          Before a control board is replaced, we verify power supply and
          isolate main-vs-UI failure. Before a thermistor is swapped, we
          test resistance at known temps. Bosch parts aren't cheap — no
          throwing money at the wrong component.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <div class="step-num">3</div>
          <h3>Manufacturer-Approved Parts Only</h3>
          <p>Aftermarket door gaskets fail within 18 months. Aftermarket
          elements burn out early. Aftermarket control boards cause phantom
          errors. We install only Bosch manufacturer-approved parts from
          authorized distributors.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <div class="step-num">4</div>
          <h3>Address the Cause, Not Just the Failure</h3>
          <p>A thermal fuse that tripped in year 5 points to ventilation
          restriction. A control board that died from surge damage points to
          surge protection being worth installing. We fix what's visible and
          flag the root cause.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <div class="step-num">5</div>
          <h3>Calibration Test Before We Leave</h3>
          <p>After any sensor or element repair, we verify oven temperature
          with a calibrated probe at multiple set points. 350°F in the
          display should read 345–355°F actual. If it doesn't, we adjust
          offset or re-diagnose.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <div class="step-num">6</div>
          <h3>90-Day Labor Warranty, 1-Year on Parts</h3>
          <p>Every Bosch wall oven repair carries a 90-day labor warranty and
          1-year warranty on installed manufacturer-approved parts. Same issue
          recurs, we come back at no charge.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
